quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  67,13,Whether you speak secretly or openly‚ÄĒHe surely knows best what is ňĻhiddenňļ in the heart
  67,14,"How could He not know His Own creation? For He ňĻaloneňļ is the Most Subtle, All-Aware"
  67,15,"He is the One Who smoothed out the earth for you, so move about in its regions and eat from His provisions. And to Him is the resurrection ňĻof allňļ"
  67,16,Do you feel secure that the One Who is in heaven will not cause the earth to swallow you up as it quakes violently
  67,17,Or do you feel secure that the One Who is in heaven will not unleash upon you a storm of stones. Only then would you know how ňĻseriousňļ My warning was
  67,18,"And certainly those before them denied ňĻas wellňļ, then how severe was My response"
  67,19,"Have they not seen the birds above them, spreading and folding their wings? None holds them up except the Most Compassionate. Indeed, He is All-Seeing of everything"
  67,20,"Also, which ňĻpowerlessňļ force will come to your help instead of the Most Compassionate? Indeed, the disbelievers are only ňĻlostňļ in delusion"
  67,21,"Or who is it that will provide for you if He withholds His provision? In fact, they persist in arrogance and aversion ňĻto the truthňļ"
  67,22,"Who is ňĻrightlyňļ guided: the one who crawls facedown or the one who walks upright on the Straight Path"
  67,23,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúHe is the One Who brought you into being and gave you hearing, sight, and intellect. ňĻYetňļ you hardly give any thanks.‚ÄĚ"
  67,24,"ňĻAlsoňļ say, ‚ÄúHe is the One Who has dispersed you ňĻallňļ over the earth, and to Him you will ňĻallňļ be gathered.‚ÄĚ"
  67,25,"ňĻStillňļ they ask ňĻthe believersňļ, ‚ÄúWhen will this threat come to pass, if what you say is true?‚ÄĚ"
  67,26,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúThat knowledge is with God alone, and I am only sent with a clear warning.‚ÄĚ"
